Optionality

Cardinally constraints with optionality

--|---- == one
-->---- == many

optional

--|-o-- == optional one
--o-<-- == optional many

mandatory

--||--- == mandatory one
--|-<-- == mandatory many

Loops
- it is fine for a loop to occur if and only if it does not cause redundancy
- if you break the loop you lose information

Tertiary relationships

Enhanced Entity Relationship Diagram (EER Diagram)
Has a super type and sub typed entity
- Super typed entity: a generic entity type that has relationships with one or more subtypes
- Sub typed entity: a sub grouping of entities in an entity type that has attributes distinct from other sub groupings